          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2018-05-30T19:53:24Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Federal Information Systems Safeguards Act of 2018</b></p> <p>This bill provides that the authority of a federal agency to take action to restrict or prohibit access to a website, or to test, deploy, or update a cybersecurity measure, if the agency determines such action is necessary to carry out its responsibilities, shall not be: (1) limited by a collective bargaining agreement or other agreement entered into before, on, or after this bill's enactment pursuant to federal labor-management relations provisions; or (2) negotiated under such provisions.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2018-03-15T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
